So.....is there a easy way to say, use the birt report design perspective but use my (specially created) report editor? Thanks

Currently, BIRT can't open report design outside of workspace in IDE enviroment, but can in RCP enviroment. So, if you want to open external report design in your, you may reference to what RCP do. Because plugin org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.rcp and plugin org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.ide can't work togther, so if you use plugin org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.ide in your application, you must define a new editor to open external report design, just simply copy from report editor in plugin org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.rcp. I have made a crack patch for plugin org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.ide which add an editor 'org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.ide.externalReportEditor', you can open a external report design like 

PlatformUI.getWorkbench( ).getActivePage( ).openEditor(new ExternalReportEditorInput(new File("D:/test.rptdesign")),"org.eclipse.birt.report.designer.ui.ide.externalReportEditor");

Hope it help.
